Kshitijko Par (क्षितिजको पार / Beyond the Horizon)
[Genre: Nepali Epic Folk Rock / Cinematic Traditional Rock]
[Tempo: ~96 BPM (shifts with dynamic intensity)]
[Key: D Minor, modulating to F Major for the final chorus]
[Vocal: Female – warm, powerful; clear high notes and intimate lows]
[Mood: Epic, spiritual, proud – blending Newari tradition with heroic modern spirit]

Instrumentation Key (for audio engine):

Flute: Wooden bamboo flute (bansuri) – airy, meditative tone (common in Nepali folk
).
Large Drum: Deep, resonant bass (like the Newar Dhimay drum
, or a large kettle drum) – booming, heartbeat-like.
Small Hand Cymbals: Bright, clashing metallic percussion (like traditional Nepali Jhyaali cymbals, used with Dhimay drums
).
Frame Drum: Shallow, slapping drum (like a Damphu frame drum
) for sharp rhythmic drive.
Electric Guitar: Clean arpeggios and distorted power chords (for modern energy).
Acoustic Guitar: Fingerpicked, warm textures.
Bass Guitar: Deep, driving foundation.
Drum Kit: Standard kit with toms and cymbals (for rock beats).
Orchestral Strings: Sweeping, cinematic backdrops.
Synth Pads: Ambient atmospheres.



[INTRO]

[A single Large Drum beats slowly, mimicking a steady heartbeat. A bansuri (bamboo flute) rises with a solemn melody, echoing in open mountain air. Distant wind sounds and tiny chimes add atmosphere. A Damphu frame drum enters with a sharp, ringing pulse, and Jhyaali cymbals join in a syncopated tinkle. An acoustic guitar weaves a gentle fingerpicked pattern. The flute repeats its motif as an electric guitar sustains a clean chord underneath, gradually building intensity.]
[Instrumental intro – blending ancient ritual sounds with modern anticipation.]

[VERSE 1]

[Drums enter with a steady, driving rock beat (hi-hat/snare). The bass guitar plays a melodic counterline. Jhyaali cymbals keep a constant shimmer. Flute weaves a graceful, rising counter-melody around the vocals.]
[Vocal (quiet determination, dreaming tone):]
धुन्दको पराल, प्राचीन स्वर गुन्जियो
ढुंगाका बाटोमा उकेरिएका वीरहरू
उनको हातमा उच्चाइएको झण्डा, कसको लागि हो?
पहाड काट्दै, नदी पार गर्दै
एउटै नाम चिच्याइरहेका थिए

[Distant flute flourish as decoration.]

[PRE-CHORUS]

[Electric guitar switches to a distorted, powerful chord progression. The drums intensify with rolling toms and crashing cymbals. The Damphu and Jhyaali accelerate. The bass drives a steady groove. Flute answers with a piercing accent.]
[Vocal (growing fierce and urgent):]
अँध्यारोमा चम्किरहेको धार
कोहीको ढाल, कोहीको आशा
आँखा बन्द गर्दा浮ि आउँछ स्वरूप
शेर हो वा बाँदर वा बुद्ध?

[CHORUS]

[Full band explodes. Distorted electric guitars play wide, open chords. The flute soars with a triumphant hook. The Large Drum and Damphu hit emphatically on downbeats. Jhyaali cymbals and hand percussion layer a festive rhythm. Orchestral strings swell under the mix.]
[Vocal (anthemic, full power):]
क्षितिजको पार दौडिन्छु
टुटेका इच्छा ताराहरू बन्छन्
सिंहराजाको भाला, बाँदरराजाको लाठी
बुद्धको करुणाले सबै समेट्छ
गर्वका साथ यो हातमा उत्कीर्ण गर्छु
अब उठ खडा होउ

[POST-CHORUS]

[Music drops to gentle texture: only acoustic guitar, flute, and soft Jhyaali rhythm. Vocal harmonies layer lightly.]
[Vocal (reverent, soothing):]
la la la… पवनको पार
la la la… ढोल गुन्जिन्छ

[VERSE 2]

[Rhythm returns with a syncopated, intricate groove (math-rock inspired). Clean electric guitar plays a muted, rapid riff. Drums interlock with offbeat fills. The flute darts playfully through the rhythm. Frame drum adds sharp accents.]
[Vocal (confident, challenging):]
हजारौं रणभूमि, हजारौं रातहरू
उसको औँलाले लेखेको विजयको पथ
पार गरिएका पर्खाल, तोडिएका जंजीर
अहिले देखिन्छ, अझै नदेखिएको चुडा

[Flute trill ascending quickly.]

[PRE-CHORUS 2]

[Electric guitar is now heavily distorted. Drums hammer a relentless beat. Jhyaali cymbals create frenzy. Bass pulses powerfully. Flute contributes urgent stabs.]
[Vocal (fierce, determined):]
भाग्यको चक्र घुम्दैछ
निर्णय लिन्छ यो हात मात्रै
सबै शत्रु भए पनि
तिमीलाई मात्र बचाउँछु

[CHORUS 2]

[Repeat Chorus arrangement with even more layers: extra strings, thicker vocal harmonies, and denser flute lines. Full power, triumphant feeling.]
